[show NS]
Between the two hands you have stoppers and the makings of a ninth trick, but only one heart stopper — your \H A — so the whole deal turns on which finesse you choose. Your two finesses sit in spades and clubs. The spade finesse — leading toward your \S KJ — loses only to West if it fails, the safe hand. The club finesse — leading toward dummy's \C KJ — loses to East, the danger hand. So take the spade finesse and steer clear of clubs; the spade play keeps East off lead even when it loses.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
You declare three notrump. East has length in hearts and your \H A is the lone stopper, so plan to keep East off lead while you develop a ninth trick.
